records.nl_statement: Let $\mathcal{T}_\alpha$ be a family of topologies on $X$. Show that there is a unique smallest topology on $X$ containing all the collections $\mathcal{T}_\alpha$.

import Mathlib

open Filter Set TopologicalSpace

records.ground_truth:
def is_topology (X : Type*) (T : Set (Set X)) :=
  univ ∈ T ∧
  (∀ s t, s ∈ T → t ∈ T → s ∩ t ∈ T) ∧
  (∀s, (∀t ∈ s, t ∈ T) → sUnion s ∈ T)

  ∀ T'', is_topology X T'' → (∀ i, T i ⊆ T'') → T' ⊆ T'' :=
